Come now.  Did Gandalf whip out his Texas Instruments calculator to see how many fireballs he could cast at the pack of wolves?  No.  He knew instinctively and so should you more or less.  Remember that this is a roleplaying game.  It´s much more enjoyable when you think you are walking through an infested dungeon than when you think you are sitting at a computer playing a video game.

As for me, I´d like to see LESS numbers in the game.  Getting a piece of armour and having the burden of putting it on and testing it to see how good it is would almost be ¨realistic.¨  

As for me, I say good riddance to annoying numbers like hitpoints, armour class, resists, etc., etc., etc.  Get me off this stupid video game and back in that dangerous dungeon!

